## Phase 6 — Offline Data & Background Sync

**Goal**: Allow users to perform actions while offline, with automatic sync when connectivity returns.

**Estimated effort**: Large  
**Dependencies**: Phase 2 (service worker), Phase 5 (push for sync confirmations)

---

### 6.1 IndexedDB Outbox Queue

#### [NEW] [offline-queue.ts](file:///c:/Users/Admin/Desktop/SurveyCorps/Projects/estate/resources/js/lib/offline-queue.ts)

A utility that:
- Opens an IndexedDB database with an `outbox` object store
- Provides `enqueue(request)` and `dequeue()` methods
- Stores failed/offline mutations (POST, PUT, DELETE) with full request data
- Tags entries with timestamps for expiration

---

### 6.2 Background Sync with Fallback

#### Service Worker: Sync Handler

In the Workbox config, register a `sync` event handler:
- On `sync` event: read all entries from IndexedDB outbox, replay them
- On success: remove from outbox, optionally notify user
- On failure: retry with exponential backoff

#### Fallback for iOS/Safari

Since Background Sync API is unsupported on Safari:
- Listen for `online` event in the React app
- Trigger `processOutboxQueue()` manually
- Use the same IndexedDB outbox as the SW-based sync

---

### 6.3 UI: Pending State Indicators

#### [NEW] [pending-badge.tsx](file:///c:/Users/Admin/Desktop/SurveyCorps/Projects/estate/resources/js/components/pwa/pending-badge.tsx)

A small component that:
- Renders a "Pending" or "Syncing..." badge on items queued offline
- Transitions to "Synced ✓" on successful background sync
- Integrates with the offline queue to reflect real-time status

---

### 6.4 Offline-First Data Patterns

Identify the most critical user actions that should work offline and implement offline-first patterns for them:

| Action | Offline Behavior |
|:---|:---|
| Browsing listings | Serve from cache (previously viewed) |
| Saving favorites | Queue in IndexedDB, sync later |
| Search | Serve cached results, show "limited results" indicator |
| Form submissions | Queue in outbox, show "pending" badge |

> [!IMPORTANT]
> The specific actions to support offline will depend on the app's core user flows. This should be scoped collaboratively based on which features matter most to users when offline.

---

### Phase 6 Verification

